# UX patterns

Every screen / feature must satisfy the checklist below. If something doesn't apply, leave a one-line comment saying why.

## Responsive

- Mobile-first. Build at 375px then scale up with `sm: md: lg:` breakpoints.
- Full-height containers use `min-h-svh` / `h-svh` (not `vh`) so mobile browser chrome doesn't clip content.
- Test at 375px, 768px, 1280px before claiming done.

## Loading & data states

- **Skeleton loaders** for any data fetch — use shadcn `<Skeleton />`, shape it to match the final layout. No bare spinners on first paint.
- **Loading states** on buttons/forms during async work: disabled + spinner + text change (e.g. "Saving...").
- **Empty states**: icon + heading + short description + primary CTA. Never render a bare empty list.
- **Error states**: friendly message + retry action; surface `ConvexError.data.message` when present.

## Mutations

- Use **optimistic updates** for any mutation where the new state is predictable (toggles, likes, reorder, delete, inline edits). Convex: `useMutation(...).withOptimisticUpdate(...)`.
- Confirm success / failure with a **Sonner toast** (`import { toast } from "sonner"`): `toast.success`, `toast.error`, or `toast.promise` for in-flight work. No `alert()`, no custom toast.

## Interaction

- **Hover states** on every clickable element (covered in `ui-styling.mdc`).
- **Command palette (⌘K / Ctrl+K)** wired globally — use shadcn `<Command />` + `<CommandDialog />`. Register a keyboard listener at the app shell level.
- **Modals / sidebars** animate open and close (Radix / shadcn primitives already do this — don't disable it). Add `motion/react` for any custom overlay.

## Navigation

- Use **view transitions** between routes (`unstable_ViewTransition` from React / Next `<Link>` view-transition support, or `motion/react` `AnimatePresence` for client-side route changes). Hard cuts are not acceptable.

## Checklist (paste at top of new feature PRs)

- [ ] mobile responsive (375 / 768 / 1280)
- [ ] `svh` for full-height
- [ ] skeleton loader
- [ ] loading state on actions
- [ ] empty state
- [ ] error state
- [ ] optimistic update (if applicable)
- [ ] sonner toast on success/failure
- [ ] hover + active + focus on all interactive elements
- [ ] modal/sidebar animations intact
- [ ] view transition on navigation
- [ ] ⌘K entries added if feature exposes navigable actions
